day4:ANCHOR TAGS(HTML links)

HTML link:A link lets users navigate from one webpage to another or to be a different page of the same page.


1.<a>
*the tag is used to create a hyperlink in HTML.
*syntax
     <a href="url">link text</a>

2.href
*stands for hypertext REFerence
*without href,the <a> tag won't act like a link.

3.opening link in new tabs
*use the target attribute:
example code:
        <a href="https://example.com"target="_blank">visit example</a>
*(target="_blank") opens link in a new tab.

4.internal page links
*links to a specific section of the same page
*give the target element an id
*link to it with (href="#section1")

5.special link types
<a href="mailto:someoneexample.com">send email</a>

6. Key Takeaways
*Links are essential for web navigation.
*<a> tag with href points where you want to go.
*You can link text, images, sections, emails, and phone numbers.
*Practice writing several links to different resources!

